# MessMaster Project Report Supplement

Full architecture, routing, models, and current feature inventory are documented in [PROJECT_CONTEXT_REPORT.md](/Users/prakharsharma/Downloads/MessMaster/PROJECT_CONTEXT_REPORT.md). This file stays focused on the implementation details most likely to matter when recreating or extending the current registration and data-bootstrap flows.

## 1. Current Mess Registration Structure

### UI sections
The active Mess Register flow contains five sections:
1. Mess Info
2. Menu Setup
3. Inventory Setup
4. Cook Setup
5. Admin Contact

### Mess Info fields
- `messName`
- `phoneNumber`
- `location`
- `messCapacity`

### Menu Setup fields
- `numberOfMenuItems`
- `menuItems[]`

### Inventory Setup fields
- `inventoryItems[]`
  - `name`
  - `category`
  - `unit`
  - `quantity`
  - `minimumQuantity`

### Cook Setup fields
- `cooks[]`
  - `name`
  - `role`
  - `contactNumber`

### Admin Contact fields
- `adminName`
- `adminEmail`
- `adminPassword`
- `adminPhoneNumber`

This four-field admin structure is the current UI and backend source-of-truth for new mess registrations.

## 2. Admin Structure and Compatibility

### Current source-of-truth
New mess registrations write:
- a `User` with role `staff`
- `Mess.adminContact`
  - `name`
  - `email`
  - `phone`

### Legacy compatibility
Older fields are still preserved/readable:
- `pointOfContact`
- `representative`

Current backend mirrors the new admin data into those legacy fields so older consumers do not break immediately.

### Migration support
Use:
- `npm run migrate:admin-contact`

to backfill `adminContact` for older mess records.

## 3. Location and Geo Support

### Current behavior
- Mess registration takes a human-readable `location` string.
- NGO registration also takes a human-readable `location` string.
- Backend geocodes that location through Nominatim.
- Coordinates are stored for geo filtering.

### Current persisted fields
#### Mess
- `location`
- `latitude`
- `longitude`
- `geo` (`Point`)

#### NGO user (`User` with role `ngo`)
- `location`
- `latitude`
- `longitude`
- `geo` (`Point`)

### Compatibility notes
- Existing text `location` remains in place for display.
- Old mess records without coordinates remain readable, but they will not appear in nearby NGO map queries until migrated or updated.

### Migration support
Use:
- `npm run migrate:location-geo`

to geocode existing mess/NGO records that only have text locations.

## 4. Menu Setup Behavior

Current menu setup logic supports:
- dynamic input generation from `numberOfMenuItems`
- delete one menu entry
- delete all menu entries
- manual add-one behavior
- trimming/cleanup before backend submission

This behavior is active in the registration UI and should be preserved.

## 5. Student Mess Selection Compatibility

The student flow remains mess-linked.

### Active constraints
- Student registration still requires `messId`.
- Student review submission still requires a mess association.
- Student review history still shows the reviewed mess name.
- Review date is generated by the server when submitted.

Any future DB or registration changes must preserve this link.

## 6. NGO Nearby Discovery

### Current implementation
- NGO dashboard uses a Leaflet map with OpenStreetMap tiles.
- Backend endpoint used by the dashboard:
  - `GET /api/v1/listings/public/nearby`
- Distance rule:
  - 20 km radius from NGO coordinates
- Only messes with active food listings appear on the map/feed.

### Legacy endpoint still present
- `GET /api/v1/listings/public/all`

This older endpoint remains for compatibility, but current NGO UI should rely on `/public/nearby`.

## 7. BioLoop Feature Notes

### Roles and auth
- New user role: `bio`
- New auth endpoints:
  - `POST /api/v1/auth/register/bio`
  - shared login through `POST /api/v1/auth/login`

### Listing lifecycle
- BioLoop uses separate marketplace models from NGO.
- Mess staff can create dumped-food or expired-food listings.
- Listings can be:
  - `scheduled`
  - `active`
  - `accepted`
  - `expired`
  - `completed`
  - `deactivated`
- Active BioLoop listings remain visible for four hours, then expire automatically if unclaimed.

### Distance filtering
- Bio admins see nearby listings within 50 km.
- Public `/bioloop` page uses a preview feed without auth.

### Staff-side UI
- Current staff dashboard includes:
  - BioLoop Waste
  - BioLoop Requests
  - BioLoop Orders
- Messes can set a default daily BioLoop logging time used for scheduled listing activation.

## 8. Seed / Reset / Migration Workflow

### Available scripts
- `npm run seed`
- `npm run reset:seed`
- `npm run migrate:admin-contact`
- `npm run migrate:location-geo`

### Operational notes
- Local MongoDB access is required through `MONGODB_URI`.
- `reset:seed` drops the current database before reseeding.
- `migrate:location-geo` requires outbound access to Nominatim.

