## 12. Menu Analysis UI Notes
- Menu Analysis still uses the same backend data and risk thresholds.
- The chart presentation is now a row-based visual instead of a traditional axis-heavy bar chart.
- Current visual behavior:
  - inline `{value} kg` labels on each bar
  - pill-shaped purple bars
  - hover highlight across the full row
  - risk distinction expressed through purple shade/glow intensity rather than introducing a new color system

## 13. Waste Log Edit/Delete Support
- Waste logs are no longer append-only.
- Current staff UI supports editing and deleting waste logs from:
  - the main Waste Log page
  - the dashboard Recent Waste Logs card
- Waste-log mutations invalidate the same analytics/dashboard queries so graphs and summary data refresh after add, edit, or delete.
